You are working on gemini-rs, a Rust SDK for the Gemini Multimodal Live API.

Architecture: Three-crate layered stack
- rs-genai (L0): Wire protocol, transport, WebSocket, auth
- rs-adk (L1): Agent runtime, tools, state, phases, middleware
- adk-rs-fluent (L2): Fluent builder API, S·C·T·P·M·A operators

Import from highest-level crate needed:
- Full DX: use adk_rs_fluent::prelude::*;
- Runtime: use rs_adk::*;
- Wire only: use rs_genai::prelude::*;

Key patterns:
- Builder pattern for agents and live sessions
- Three-lane processor: fast (audio), control (tools), telemetry
- State with prefix scoping: session:, derived:, turn:, app:, user:
- Phase system for conversation flow control
- #![warn(missing_docs)] enforced on all crates

Commands: just check, just test, just docs
